d end-to-end using maximum likelihood estimation on historical crime logs, with auxiliary supervision from semantic embeddings of neighborhood features. We evaluate the system on large-scale datasets from multiple cities, measuring performance in terms of hyperedge prediction accuracy (type, participants, time), forecasting precision-recall curves, and qualitative interpretability via case studies. This work bridges symbolic reasoning about urban systems with deep probabilistic modeling, offering both scientific advancement and practical utility for predictive policing and urban safety planning.",
